In feature-based [[phonology]], '''delayed release''' is a [[distinctive feature]] representing how quickly the closure in a non-[[continuant]] consonant is released. It separates [[stop consonant|stops]], which are [&minus;delayed release], from [[affricate]]s, which are [+delayed release], both of which are [&minus;[[sonorant]], &minus;[[continuant]]]. 

